      <main role="main">
        <section class="">
    <div class="layout-semibreve">		
        <header class="badge-heading badge-blue">
            <h2>The Opportunity</h2>
        </header>
        
        <div class="layout-gutter">
        
            <div class="layout-minim">
            
                <p>The $172 billion government IT spending market is ripe and ready for disruption. It needs new tools and technologies that provide high value at reasonable costs — and it needs new entrepreneurs and businesses to provide them. The Code for America Accelerator is looking for govtech focused companies and entrepreneurs to do just this. </p>
				
				<p>Code for America partners with local government to use modern technology tools and approaches to foster collaboration with their community, improve internal government processes and service delivery, and more effectively and efficiently address community needs. Companies are a crucial part of creating governments that work for the people, by the people, in the 21st century. </p>
				
                </div>
            
            <div class="layout-minim">
				<img class="teaser-image" src="/media/images/geeks_accelerator_apply/people_at_work_small.jpg">
                <ul class="list-gappy list-inline list-buttons">
                
                    <li><a href="http://codeforamerica.org/geeks/accelerator-faq/" class="button">Learn more in our FAQ</a></li>
                
                </ul>              
            
            </div>
        
        </div>
        
    </div>

</section>



            
<section class="slab-blue">
    <div class="layout-semibreve">
        <div class="highlight">
            <blockquote>
                <p>The Accelerator completely elevated our overall sense of purpose. We already knew that we were disrupting the state of technology for a specific pain point, and the Accelerator helped us realize the part we can play to transform government into a platform on which vendors like us, citizens, and public sector employees work together to improve society.</p>
            </blockquote>
            <p class="attribute">Anil Chawla, CEO <a href="http://archivesocial.com">ArchiveSocial</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>


<section class="slab-gray">
	<div class="layout-semibreve">
        <header class="badge-heading badge-graph badge-dark-blue">
            <h2>Benefits</h2>
        </header>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Training and mentorship:</strong> World-class content and mentorship from CfA’s extensive network of leaders in the technology and public administration space. Last year, mentors spent over 200 hours with the companies, on topics such as sales, lead generation, UX, marketing, product and fundraising. </li>
				<li><strong>Funding:</strong> Companies receive $25,000 USD per team to grow their businesses. As is customary with many Accelerators, our investment stake will depend on the stage and structure of the company, and will be determined prior to acceptance of any company in the Accelerator. </li>
				<li><strong>Office space:</strong> Companies have access to our coworking space and meeting rooms. Additionally, every month for the course of the program, you'll convene at <a href="http://goo.gl/maps/IqhhH">Code for America HQ</a> in downtown San Francisco for a week of mentorship, meetings and training. Many teams travel back and forth between SF and their hometowns for the duration of this program.</li>
				<li><strong>Services and support:</strong> Your team will gain special access to product credits and training from some of our <a href="http://codeforamerica.org/supporters/" title="Supporters — Code for America">donors and sponsors</a></li>
				<li><strong>Network and publicity:</strong> Access to CfA’s extensive government network, including an opportunity to present, as well as participate in the Civic Tech Fair at the <a href="http://codeforamerica.org/summit/" title="Code for America 2014 Summit — Code for America">2014 CfA Summit</a>. Your team will receive 3 tickets to the Summit, which included over 80 governments in 2013. </li>
				<li></li>
			</ul>
	</div>
	
		<div class="layout-centered">			 	
			<h6>Still have questions? Email <a href="mailto:companies@codeforamerica.org">companies[at]codeforamerica.org</a></h6>
		</div>
</section>

	
